subSubSection.paragraph:
Teeth moderately large, conical (
Fig. 3B
). Intermaxillary in about four transverse rows, separated from maxillary and vomerine teeth, mostly excluded from closed mouth. Maxillary and mandibular teeth in bands, wider anteriorly, roughly in four or five rows, narrower posteriorly; in 1 to 2 rows; outermost teeth slightly larger than innermost. Vomerine teeth forming a small oval patch, 3 irregular rows of small teeth followed by several large blunt teeth, roughly in 2 rows.
